{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a92a47b5-55dc-49cd-9732-4503065b85b7","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, .NET Core 3.1, and .NET 5.0** — but with important caveats:\n\n1. **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is out of support. MSTest v3 may still build against it, but it's not a supported target.\n2. **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is also end-of-life. MSTest v3.x drops support for older runtimes in later minor versions.\n3. **`net462`** — This should still be supported in MSTest v3.\n\n**Recommendations before migrating:**\n\n- Update `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` or `net8.0`\n- Update `net5.0` → `net6.0` or `net8.0`\n- Then upgrade to MSTest v3 (`MSTest` meta-package replaces the separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` references)\n\n**Also note MSTest v3 breaking changes:**\n- Some assertions have stricter behavior\n- `[TestClass]` is now required (previously optional in some scenarios)\n- The recommended package is now just `MSTest` (single package) instead of separate `TestFramework` + `TestAdapter`\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3 compatibility?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9d97e0c-ce01-49c9-8863-62e302b47ad4","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"BC2A:48F1C:21CE662:25979D7:69FAA837"},"id":"811f27b3-515d-48df-b12b-4c2b9657e496","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:32:31.486Z","parentId":"1b8d44e5-5fc5-4129-aabd-784f8f26e391"}
